  <Properties>
    <contentGrid>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f170b29c-338f-4ab8-a5c4-f72c90826f69",
      "key": "48acdd1b-f4cb-4259-acc7-25b4ced607e3",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "c345e5ce-768f-47e0-968a-e7859dbe0b07",
      "key": "9bb92538-a5b9-497f-a2f3-96093f5ebc88",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "3d999ce2-8ce6-42fa-ae9c-5b102b4f7e6a",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "What It Does"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Displays a single image from the Umbraco media library"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe Image feature lets content editors pick a single image from the Umbraco media library and display it on the page. The image renders as a full-width, responsive element that scales to fit its container while maintaining its aspect ratio using \u003Ccode\u003Eobject-fit: cover\u003C/code\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELike all features in UmBootstrap, the Image block supports the standard compositions \u2014 editors can add a title, description, and summary around the image. This makes it useful for captioned images, hero banners, or any visual content that needs accompanying text.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureSummary",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Image blocks without a Feature Title are automatically excluded from the in-page navigation picker."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "e2b0b66e-d31e-4e96-925a-338e887c117b",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "How It Works"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Uses Umbraco\u0027s Media Picker with the strongly-typed ModelsBuilder model"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe view accesses the image through the strongly-typed \u003Ccode\u003EModel.Content.Image\u003C/code\u003E property, which returns a \u003Ccode\u003EMediaWithCrops\u003C/code\u003E object from Umbraco\u0027s Media Picker 3. The \u003Ccode\u003EMediaUrl()\u003C/code\u003E extension method generates the URL for the selected image.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe image is rendered with \u003Ccode\u003Eobject-fit: cover\u003C/code\u003E and \u003Ccode\u003Ewidth: 100%\u003C/code\u003E so it fills its container regardless of the original image dimensions. A \u003Ccode\u003Erounded-3\u003C/code\u003E Bootstrap class adds subtle rounded corners.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf no image is selected, the view displays a \u0022Missing image\u0022 message as a fallback \u2014 useful during development but something you may want to handle differently in production.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureSummary",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Add a title like \u0022Gallery\u0022 or \u0022Product Photos\u0022 if you want image sections to appear in navigation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "c4b3a613-0d2c-4470-8d06-f7efea52d6e0",
      "key": "2b34ac9e-de8f-4900-a0cd-2dd2fc8ac911",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyNavigationInPageItems",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": [
            "3d999ce2-8ce6-42fa-ae9c-5b102b4f7e6a",
            "e2b0b66e-d31e-4e96-925a-338e887c117b"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
